sentences: Caleb Perry Johnson (born April 23, 1991) is an American singer who won the thirteenth season of American Idol.
After leaving his label, he formed another group, Caleb Johnson and the Ramblin' Saints, and in 2019, the group self-released its first album, Born from Southern Ground.
Caleb Johnson was born on April 23, 1991, to David and Tamra Johnson in Asheville, North Carolina.
He attended Clyde A. Erwin High School in Asheville and graduated in 2009.
After graduating Erwin High School in Asheville, North Carolina, on June 30, 2009, Caleb Johnson first joined a band called Rock Bottom as its lead singer.
Elijah Hooker released its self-titled debut album Elijah Hooker in June 2013.
2011–14: American Idol ===
He first auditioned for the tenth season of American Idol in 2011.
In 2012, Johnson auditioned for the eleventh season and made it to the Top 42.
Johnson auditioned again in 2014 for the thirteenth season and made it to the top 20.

A year later, he joined his friend Josh Sawyer in rock band called Elijah Hooker and became its lead vocalist.
Johnson auditioned for American Idol three times in four years.
He was put through to Hollywood Week and was in a Hollywood group with James Durbin.
He took the following year off from auditioning to improve on his stage presence.
Johnson got positive feedback from the judges every week, had strong performances, and became the only finalist in the season to never land in the bottom 3 prior to reaching the finale.
The album was recorded in three weeks and Johnson collaborated with musicians such as Howard Benson, Aloe Blacc, Brian Howes, Blair Daly and James Michael.
